<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN394-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇīyum tuṟaiyum avai. kaṭainilaiyāyiṉa vellām pāṭāṇṭiṇai. cōḻiya ēṉāti tirukkuṭṭuvaṉaik kōṉāṭṭu eṟiccilūr māṭalaṉ maturaikkumaraṉār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN394">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>cilaiyulāy nimirnta cāntupaṭu mārpi</l>
<l>ṉolikatir kaḻaṉi veṇkuṭaik kiḻavōṉ</l>
<l>valituñcu taṭakkai vāyvāṭ kuṭṭuvaṉ</l>
<l>vaḷḷiya ṉātal vaiyakam pukaḻiṉu</l>
<l>muḷḷa lōmpumi ṉuyarmoḻip pulavīr</l>
<l>yāṉum, iruṇilāk kaḻinta pakalcey vaikaṟai</l>
<l>yorukaṇ mākkiṇai teḷirppa voṟṟip</l>
<l>pāṭimiḻ muraci ṉiyaṟērt tantai</l>
<l>vāṭā vañci pāṭiṉē ṉāka</l>
<l>vakamali yuvakaiyō ṭaṇukal vēṇṭik</l>
<l>koṉṟuciṉan taṇiyāp pulavunāṟu maruppiṉ</l>
<l>veñciṉa vēḻa nalkiṉa ṉañci</l>
<l>yāṉatu peyarttaṉe ṉākat tāṉatu</l>
<l>ciṟiteṉa vuṇarntamai nāṇip piṟitumōr</l>
<l>peruṅkaḷiṟu nalki yōṉē vataṉkoṇ</l>
<l>ṭirumpē rokkal perumpulam puṟiṉun</l>
<l>tuṉṉarum parici ṟarumeṉa</l>
<l>veṉṟuñ cellēṉavaṉ kuṉṟukeḻu nāṭṭē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The lord of a white parasol, [his] paddy fields with sprouting ears, (2)</l>
<l>with a sandal-smeared chest, who moves about [and] holds up a bow, (1)</l>
<l>Kuṭṭuvaṉ with an excellent sword [and] broad hands where strength lies dormant, (3)</l>
<l>more than [his] fame in the world of being munificent (4)</l>
<l>beware of thinking [of him], o scholars with lofty words. (5)</l>
<l>When I, too, at day-making dawn when the moonlit darkness has passed (6)</l>
<l>pressing, so that it sounded, [my] one-eyed big Kiṇai drum, (7)</l>
<l>sang in unfading Vañci (9)</l>
<l>the father with advancing chariots [and] a song-emitting drum, (8)</l>
<l>when, wanting to come near with joy filling [my] breast, (10)</l>
<l>afraid that he would grant an elephant bull in hot anger, (12)</l>
<l>with flesh-reeking tusks who anger had not cooled down after killing, (11)</l>
<l>I went back from it, he was ashamed a little</l>
<l>because of perceiving that, [and] granted another</l>
<l>big elephant bull. Taking that in, (13d-15) </l>
<l>also [my] great big kinfolk experienced great loneliness, (16)</l>
<l>thinking “he will give present difficult to approach”, (17)</l>
<l>I will never [again] go to his mountainous land.</l>
</lg>
